<item>
            <title>[OAK-8117] NPE when adding ACE with restrictions and remapped namespaces</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-8117</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stillalex&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stillalex&quot;&gt;stillalex&lt;/a&gt;, just ran into an NPE when adding an ACE including some restriction. The reason is a tiny bug in the &lt;tt&gt;ACL&lt;/tt&gt; implementation that mistakenly uses the &lt;em&gt;oakName&lt;/em&gt; to retrieve the value/values from the passed restriction map. It should obviously use the key of the map, which corresponds to the &lt;em&gt;jcrName&lt;/em&gt;. in other words: the bug only shows up when running tests with re-mapped namespaces.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;proposed fix attached. will attach a test case illustrating the issue later on.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
