                            <comment id="16791579" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2019 11:03:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;sure, no concerns here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16791588" author="anchela" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2019 11:17:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stillalex&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stillalex&quot;&gt;stillalex&lt;/a&gt;, thanks a lot! will fix it right away. if at some point we have a little time left, we could change the default &lt;tt&gt;NamePathMapper&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;AbstractSecurityTest&lt;/tt&gt; or in those sub-tests that we know take or expose JCR paths, that would quite certainly spot additional issues. but obviously it&apos;s quite an act to adjust paths used all across the many tests to make sure they always conform to Jcr/Oak-Path depending on the API used at hand.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
